text: Honey Boo Boo Just Released a Rap Video Grab your Go-Go Juice - Honey Boo Boo just released a rap video.The 10-year-old star of ... Comment Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 9:10 AM Updated Oct 1, 2015 at 12:31 PM By TV Guide Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 9:10 AM Updated Oct 1, 2015 at 12:31 PM Grab your Go-Go Juice - Honey Boo Boo just released a rap video. The 10-year-old star of Here Comes Honey Boo Boo has debuted a new song, "Movin' Up," under her real name, Alana Thompson. The video features Thompson bopping around with her mother, "Mama June" Shannon , Shannon's on-again-off-again boyfriend Mike "Sugar Bear" Thompson, and Alana's 16-year-old sister Lauryn (aka Pumpkin). "I'm just a small-town girl / Living in my princess world," Alana yells in the song's opening lines. The video is a sight to behold in itself, and the song is catchy, if nothing else. The clip was produced by viral video guru Adam Barta, who has previously collaborated with Margaret Cho , Anthony Weiner's sexting partner Sydney Leathers, and "Tan Mom" Patricia Kentcil. Here Comes Honey Boo Boo was canceled last year after reports surfaced that Mama June was dating a convicted child molester.
